(17, '24449', 'abstract2', 'category 1', 'type 1', 'Dr kale', '<p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif;\"><b>Cancer</b> is a group of diseases involving abnormal <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cell_growth\" title=\"Cell growth\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">cell growth</a> with the potential to invade or spread to other parts of the body.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-NCI2014_8-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-NCI2014-8\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[8]</a></sup> These contrast with <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Benign_tumor\" title=\"Benign tumor\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">benign tumors</a>, which do not spread.<sup id=\"cite_ref-NCI2014_8-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-NCI2014-8\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[8]</a></sup> Possible <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer_signs_and_symptoms\" title=\"Cancer signs and symptoms\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">signs and symptoms</a> include a lump, abnormal bleeding, prolonged cough, unexplained <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Weight_loss\" title=\"Weight loss\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">weight loss</a> and a change in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Defecation\" title=\"Defecation\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">bowel movements</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-NHS2012_1-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-NHS2012-1\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[1]</a></sup> While these symptoms may indicate cancer, they can also have other causes.<sup id=\"cite_ref-NHS2012_1-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-NHS2012-1\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[1]</a></sup> Over 100 types of cancers affect humans.<sup id=\"cite_ref-NCI2014_8-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-NCI2014-8\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[8]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tobacco_use\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Tobacco use\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Tobacco use</a> is the cause of about 22% of cancer deaths.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-3\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup> Another 10% are due to <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Obesity\" title=\"Obesity\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">obesity</a>, poor <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diet_(nutrition)\" title=\"Diet (nutrition)\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">diet</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sedentary_lifestyle\" title=\"Sedentary lifestyle\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">lack of physical activity</a> or <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alcohol_abuse\" title=\"Alcohol abuse\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">excessive drinking</a> of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alcohol_(drug)\" title=\"Alcohol (drug)\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">alcohol</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-4\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-9\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[9]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-10\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[10]</a></sup> Other factors include certain infections, exposure to <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ionizing_radiation\" title=\"Ionizing radiation\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">ionizing radiation</a> and environmental pollutants.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Enviro2008_3-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-Enviro2008-3\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[3]</a></sup> In the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Developing_country\" title=\"Developing country\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">developing world</a>, 15% of cancers are due to infections such as <i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Helicobacter_pylori\" title=\"Helicobacter pylori\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Helicobacter pylori</a></i>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hepatitis_B\" title=\"Hepatitis B\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">hepatitis B</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hepatitis_C\" title=\"Hepatitis C\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">hepatitis C</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_papillomavirus_infection\" title=\"Human papillomavirus infection\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">human papillomavirus infection</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Epstein%E2%80%93Barr_virus\" title=\"Epstein–Barr virus\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Epstein–Barr virus</a>and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HIV\" title=\"HIV\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">human immunodeficiency virus</a> (HIV).<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-5\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup> These factors act, at least partly, by changing the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gene\" title=\"Gene\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">genes</a> of a cell.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Bio_11-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Bio-11\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[11]</a></sup> Typically, many genetic changes are required before cancer develops.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Bio_11-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Bio-11\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[11]</a></sup> Approximately 5–10% of cancers are due to inherited genetic defects from a person\'s parents.<sup id=\"cite_ref-ACS-heredity_12-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-ACS-heredity-12\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[12]</a></sup> Cancer can be detected by certain signs and symptoms or <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer_screening\" title=\"Cancer screening\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">screening tests</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-6\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup> It is then typically further investigated by <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medical_imaging\" title=\"Medical imaging\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">medical imaging</a> and confirmed by <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biopsy\" title=\"Biopsy\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">biopsy</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-13\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-13\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[13]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif;\">Many cancers can be prevented by not smoking, maintaining a healthy weight, not drinking too much <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alcohol_(drug)\" title=\"Alcohol (drug)\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">alcohol</a>, eating plenty of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vegetables\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Vegetables\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">vegetables</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fruits\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Fruits\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">fruits</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Whole_grains\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Whole grains\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">whole grains</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vaccination\" title=\"Vaccination\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">vaccination</a> against certain infectious diseases, not eating too much <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Processed_meat\" title=\"Processed meat\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">processed</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Red_meat\" title=\"Red meat\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">red meat</a> and avoiding too much <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sunlight\" title=\"Sunlight\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">sunlight</a> exposure.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Kushi2012_14-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-Kushi2012-14\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[14]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-15\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-15\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[15]</a></sup> Early detection through <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer_screening\" title=\"Cancer screening\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">screening</a> is useful for <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cervical_cancer\" title=\"Cervical cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">cervical</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colorectal_cancer\" title=\"Colorectal cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">colorectal cancer</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Scr_16-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Scr-16\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[16]</a></sup> The benefits of screening in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Breast_cancer\" title=\"Breast cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">breast cancer</a> are controversial.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Scr_16-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Scr-16\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[16]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Got2013_17-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-Got2013-17\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[17]</a></sup> Cancer is often treated with some combination of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Radiation_therapy\" title=\"Radiation therapy\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">radiation therapy</a>, surgery, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chemotherapy\" title=\"Chemotherapy\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">chemotherapy</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Targeted_therapy\" title=\"Targeted therapy\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">targeted therapy</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-7\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-TCT2018_4-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-TCT2018-4\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[4]</a></sup> Pain and symptom management are an important part of care.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-8\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup> <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Palliative_care\" title=\"Palliative care\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Palliative care</a>is particularly important in people with advanced disease.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-9\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup> The chance of survival depends on the type of cancer and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer_staging\" title=\"Cancer staging\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">extent of disease</a> at the start of treatment.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Bio_11-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Bio-11\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[11]</a></sup> In children under 15 at diagnosis, the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Five-year_survival_rate\" title=\"Five-year survival rate\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">five-year survival rate</a> in the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Developed_world\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Developed world\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">developed world</a> is on average 80%.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Peads_18-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Peads-18\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[18]</a></sup> For cancer in the United States, the average five-year survival rate is 66%.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Seer2014_5-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-Seer2014-5\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[5]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif;\">In 2015, about 90.5 million people had cancer.<sup id=\"cite_ref-GBD2015Pre_6-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-GBD2015Pre-6\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[6]</a></sup> About 14.1 million new cases occur a year (not including <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skin_cancer\" title=\"Skin cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">skin cancer other than melanoma</a>).<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Bio_11-3\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Bio-11\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[11]</a></sup> It caused about 8.8 million deaths (15.7% of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Causes_of_death\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Causes of death\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">deaths</a>).<sup id=\"cite_ref-GBD2015De_7-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-GBD2015De-7\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[7]</a></sup> The most common types of cancer in males are <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lung_cancer\" title=\"Lung cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">lung cancer</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prostate_cancer\" title=\"Prostate cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">prostate cancer</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colorectal_cancer\" title=\"Colorectal cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">colorectal cancer</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stomach_cancer\" title=\"Stomach cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">stomach cancer</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014_19-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014-19\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[19]</a></sup> In females, the most common types are breast cancer, colorectal cancer, lung cancer and cervical cancer.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Bio_11-4\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Bio-11\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[11]</a></sup> If <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skin_cancer\" title=\"Skin cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">skin cancer</a> other than <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Melanoma\" title=\"Melanoma\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">melanoma</a> were included in total new cancer cases each year, it would account for around 40% of cases.<sup id=\"cite_ref-20\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-20\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[20]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Cak2012_21-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-Cak2012-21\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[21]</a></sup> In children, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Acute_lymphoblastic_leukemia\" title=\"Acute lymphoblastic leukemia\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">acute lymphoblastic leukemia</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brain_tumors\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brain tumors\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">brain tumors</a> are most common, except in Africa where <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-Hodgkin_lymphoma\" title=\"Non-Hodgkin lymphoma\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">non-Hodgkin lymphoma</a> occurs more often.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Peads_18-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Peads-18\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[18]</a></sup> In 2012, about 165,000 children under 15 years of age were diagnosed with cancer.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014_19-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014-19\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[19]</a></sup> The risk of cancer increases significantly with age, and many cancers occur more commonly in developed countries.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Bio_11-5\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Bio-11\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[11]</a></sup> Rates are increasing as <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Population_ageing\" title=\"Population ageing\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">more people live to an old age</a> and as lifestyle changes occur in the developing world.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Epi11_22-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-Epi11-22\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[22]</a></sup> The financial costs of cancer were estimated at $1.16 trillion <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_dollar\" title=\"United States dollar\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">USD</a> per year as of 2010.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Eco_23-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Eco-23\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[23]</a></sup></p>', '<p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif;\"><b>Cancer</b> is a group of diseases involving abnormal <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cell_growth\" title=\"Cell growth\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">cell growth</a> with the potential to invade or spread to other parts of the body.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-NCI2014_8-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-NCI2014-8\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[8]</a></sup> These contrast with <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Benign_tumor\" title=\"Benign tumor\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">benign tumors</a>, which do not spread.<sup id=\"cite_ref-NCI2014_8-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-NCI2014-8\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[8]</a></sup> Possible <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer_signs_and_symptoms\" title=\"Cancer signs and symptoms\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">signs and symptoms</a> include a lump, abnormal bleeding, prolonged cough, unexplained <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Weight_loss\" title=\"Weight loss\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">weight loss</a> and a change in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Defecation\" title=\"Defecation\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">bowel movements</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-NHS2012_1-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-NHS2012-1\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[1]</a></sup> While these symptoms may indicate cancer, they can also have other causes.<sup id=\"cite_ref-NHS2012_1-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-NHS2012-1\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[1]</a></sup> Over 100 types of cancers affect humans.<sup id=\"cite_ref-NCI2014_8-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-NCI2014-8\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[8]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tobacco_use\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Tobacco use\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Tobacco use</a> is the cause of about 22% of cancer deaths.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-3\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup> Another 10% are due to <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Obesity\" title=\"Obesity\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">obesity</a>, poor <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diet_(nutrition)\" title=\"Diet (nutrition)\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">diet</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sedentary_lifestyle\" title=\"Sedentary lifestyle\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">lack of physical activity</a> or <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alcohol_abuse\" title=\"Alcohol abuse\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">excessive drinking</a> of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alcohol_(drug)\" title=\"Alcohol (drug)\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">alcohol</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-4\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-9\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[9]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-10\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[10]</a></sup> Other factors include certain infections, exposure to <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ionizing_radiation\" title=\"Ionizing radiation\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">ionizing radiation</a> and environmental pollutants.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Enviro2008_3-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-Enviro2008-3\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[3]</a></sup> In the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Developing_country\" title=\"Developing country\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">developing world</a>, 15% of cancers are due to infections such as <i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Helicobacter_pylori\" title=\"Helicobacter pylori\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Helicobacter pylori</a></i>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hepatitis_B\" title=\"Hepatitis B\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">hepatitis B</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hepatitis_C\" title=\"Hepatitis C\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">hepatitis C</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_papillomavirus_infection\" title=\"Human papillomavirus infection\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">human papillomavirus infection</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Epstein%E2%80%93Barr_virus\" title=\"Epstein–Barr virus\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Epstein–Barr virus</a>and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HIV\" title=\"HIV\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">human immunodeficiency virus</a> (HIV).<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-5\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup> These factors act, at least partly, by changing the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gene\" title=\"Gene\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">genes</a> of a cell.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Bio_11-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Bio-11\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[11]</a></sup> Typically, many genetic changes are required before cancer develops.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Bio_11-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Bio-11\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[11]</a></sup> Approximately 5–10% of cancers are due to inherited genetic defects from a person\'s parents.<sup id=\"cite_ref-ACS-heredity_12-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-ACS-heredity-12\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[12]</a></sup> Cancer can be detected by certain signs and symptoms or <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer_screening\" title=\"Cancer screening\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">screening tests</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-6\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup> It is then typically further investigated by <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medical_imaging\" title=\"Medical imaging\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">medical imaging</a> and confirmed by <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biopsy\" title=\"Biopsy\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">biopsy</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-13\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-13\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[13]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif;\">Many cancers can be prevented by not smoking, maintaining a healthy weight, not drinking too much <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alcohol_(drug)\" title=\"Alcohol (drug)\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">alcohol</a>, eating plenty of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vegetables\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Vegetables\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">vegetables</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fruits\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Fruits\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">fruits</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Whole_grains\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Whole grains\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">whole grains</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vaccination\" title=\"Vaccination\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">vaccination</a> against certain infectious diseases, not eating too much <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Processed_meat\" title=\"Processed meat\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">processed</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Red_meat\" title=\"Red meat\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">red meat</a> and avoiding too much <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sunlight\" title=\"Sunlight\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">sunlight</a> exposure.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Kushi2012_14-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-Kushi2012-14\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[14]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-15\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-15\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[15]</a></sup> Early detection through <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer_screening\" title=\"Cancer screening\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">screening</a> is useful for <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cervical_cancer\" title=\"Cervical cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">cervical</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colorectal_cancer\" title=\"Colorectal cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">colorectal cancer</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Scr_16-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Scr-16\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[16]</a></sup> The benefits of screening in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Breast_cancer\" title=\"Breast cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">breast cancer</a> are controversial.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Scr_16-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Scr-16\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[16]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Got2013_17-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-Got2013-17\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[17]</a></sup> Cancer is often treated with some combination of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Radiation_therapy\" title=\"Radiation therapy\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">radiation therapy</a>, surgery, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chemotherapy\" title=\"Chemotherapy\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">chemotherapy</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Targeted_therapy\" title=\"Targeted therapy\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">targeted therapy</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-7\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-TCT2018_4-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-TCT2018-4\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[4]</a></sup> Pain and symptom management are an important part of care.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-8\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup> <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Palliative_care\" title=\"Palliative care\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Palliative care</a>is particularly important in people with advanced disease.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-9\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup> The chance of survival depends on the type of cancer and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer_staging\" title=\"Cancer staging\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">extent of disease</a> at the start of treatment.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Bio_11-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Bio-11\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[11]</a></sup> In children under 15 at diagnosis, the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Five-year_survival_rate\" title=\"Five-year survival rate\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">five-year survival rate</a> in the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Developed_world\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Developed world\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">developed world</a> is on average 80%.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Peads_18-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Peads-18\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[18]</a></sup> For cancer in the United States, the average five-year survival rate is 66%.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Seer2014_5-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-Seer2014-5\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[5]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif;\">In 2015, about 90.5 million people had cancer.<sup id=\"cite_ref-GBD2015Pre_6-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-GBD2015Pre-6\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[6]</a></sup> About 14.1 million new cases occur a year (not including <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skin_cancer\" title=\"Skin cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">skin cancer other than melanoma</a>).<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Bio_11-3\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Bio-11\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[11]</a></sup> It caused about 8.8 million deaths (15.7% of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Causes_of_death\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Causes of death\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">deaths</a>).<sup id=\"cite_ref-GBD2015De_7-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-GBD2015De-7\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[7]</a></sup> The most common types of cancer in males are <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lung_cancer\" title=\"Lung cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">lung cancer</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prostate_cancer\" title=\"Prostate cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">prostate cancer</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colorectal_cancer\" title=\"Colorectal cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">colorectal cancer</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stomach_cancer\" title=\"Stomach cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">stomach cancer</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014_19-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014-19\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[19]</a></sup> In females, the most common types are breast cancer, colorectal cancer, lung cancer and cervical cancer.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Bio_11-4\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Bio-11\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[11]</a></sup> If <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skin_cancer\" title=\"Skin cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">skin cancer</a> other than <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Melanoma\" title=\"Melanoma\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">melanoma</a> were included in total new cancer cases each year, it would account for around 40% of cases.<sup id=\"cite_ref-20\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-20\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[20]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Cak2012_21-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-Cak2012-21\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[21]</a></sup> In children, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Acute_lymphoblastic_leukemia\" title=\"Acute lymphoblastic leukemia\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">acute lymphoblastic leukemia</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brain_tumors\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brain tumors\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">brain tumors</a> are most common, except in Africa where <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-Hodgkin_lymphoma\" title=\"Non-Hodgkin lymphoma\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">non-Hodgkin lymphoma</a> occurs more often.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Peads_18-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Peads-18\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[18]</a></sup> In 2012, about 165,000 children under 15 years of age were diagnosed with cancer.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014_19-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014-19\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[19]</a></sup> The risk of cancer increases significantly with age, and many cancers occur more commonly in developed countries.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Bio_11-5\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Bio-11\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[11]</a></sup> Rates are increasing as <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Population_ageing\" title=\"Population ageing\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">more people live to an old age</a> and as lifestyle changes occur in the developing world.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Epi11_22-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-Epi11-22\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[22]</a></sup> The financial costs of cancer were estimated at $1.16 trillion <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_dollar\" title=\"United States dollar\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">USD</a> per year as of 2010.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Eco_23-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Eco-23\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[23]</a></sup></p>', '<p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif;\"><b>Cancer</b> is a group of diseases involving abnormal <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cell_growth\" title=\"Cell growth\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">cell growth</a> with the potential to invade or spread to other parts of the body.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-NCI2014_8-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-NCI2014-8\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[8]</a></sup> These contrast with <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Benign_tumor\" title=\"Benign tumor\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">benign tumors</a>, which do not spread.<sup id=\"cite_ref-NCI2014_8-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-NCI2014-8\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[8]</a></sup> Possible <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer_signs_and_symptoms\" title=\"Cancer signs and symptoms\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">signs and symptoms</a> include a lump, abnormal bleeding, prolonged cough, unexplained <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Weight_loss\" title=\"Weight loss\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">weight loss</a> and a change in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Defecation\" title=\"Defecation\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">bowel movements</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-NHS2012_1-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-NHS2012-1\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[1]</a></sup> While these symptoms may indicate cancer, they can also have other causes.<sup id=\"cite_ref-NHS2012_1-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-NHS2012-1\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[1]</a></sup> Over 100 types of cancers affect humans.<sup id=\"cite_ref-NCI2014_8-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-NCI2014-8\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[8]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tobacco_use\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Tobacco use\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Tobacco use</a> is the cause of about 22% of cancer deaths.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-3\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup> Another 10% are due to <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Obesity\" title=\"Obesity\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">obesity</a>, poor <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diet_(nutrition)\" title=\"Diet (nutrition)\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">diet</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sedentary_lifestyle\" title=\"Sedentary lifestyle\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">lack of physical activity</a> or <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alcohol_abuse\" title=\"Alcohol abuse\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">excessive drinking</a> of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alcohol_(drug)\" title=\"Alcohol (drug)\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">alcohol</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-4\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-9\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[9]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-10\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[10]</a></sup> Other factors include certain infections, exposure to <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ionizing_radiation\" title=\"Ionizing radiation\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">ionizing radiation</a> and environmental pollutants.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Enviro2008_3-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-Enviro2008-3\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[3]</a></sup> In the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Developing_country\" title=\"Developing country\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">developing world</a>, 15% of cancers are due to infections such as <i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Helicobacter_pylori\" title=\"Helicobacter pylori\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Helicobacter pylori</a></i>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hepatitis_B\" title=\"Hepatitis B\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">hepatitis B</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hepatitis_C\" title=\"Hepatitis C\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">hepatitis C</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_papillomavirus_infection\" title=\"Human papillomavirus infection\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">human papillomavirus infection</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Epstein%E2%80%93Barr_virus\" title=\"Epstein–Barr virus\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Epstein–Barr virus</a>and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HIV\" title=\"HIV\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">human immunodeficiency virus</a> (HIV).<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-5\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup> These factors act, at least partly, by changing the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gene\" title=\"Gene\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">genes</a> of a cell.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Bio_11-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Bio-11\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[11]</a></sup> Typically, many genetic changes are required before cancer develops.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Bio_11-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Bio-11\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[11]</a></sup> Approximately 5–10% of cancers are due to inherited genetic defects from a person\'s parents.<sup id=\"cite_ref-ACS-heredity_12-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-ACS-heredity-12\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[12]</a></sup> Cancer can be detected by certain signs and symptoms or <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer_screening\" title=\"Cancer screening\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">screening tests</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-6\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup> It is then typically further investigated by <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medical_imaging\" title=\"Medical imaging\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">medical imaging</a> and confirmed by <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biopsy\" title=\"Biopsy\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">biopsy</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-13\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-13\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[13]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif;\">Many cancers can be prevented by not smoking, maintaining a healthy weight, not drinking too much <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alcohol_(drug)\" title=\"Alcohol (drug)\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">alcohol</a>, eating plenty of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vegetables\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Vegetables\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">vegetables</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fruits\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Fruits\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">fruits</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Whole_grains\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Whole grains\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">whole grains</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vaccination\" title=\"Vaccination\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">vaccination</a> against certain infectious diseases, not eating too much <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Processed_meat\" title=\"Processed meat\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">processed</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Red_meat\" title=\"Red meat\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">red meat</a> and avoiding too much <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sunlight\" title=\"Sunlight\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">sunlight</a> exposure.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Kushi2012_14-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-Kushi2012-14\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[14]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-15\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-15\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[15]</a></sup> Early detection through <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer_screening\" title=\"Cancer screening\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">screening</a> is useful for <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cervical_cancer\" title=\"Cervical cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">cervical</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colorectal_cancer\" title=\"Colorectal cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">colorectal cancer</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Scr_16-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Scr-16\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[16]</a></sup> The benefits of screening in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Breast_cancer\" title=\"Breast cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">breast cancer</a> are controversial.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Scr_16-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Scr-16\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[16]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Got2013_17-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-Got2013-17\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[17]</a></sup> Cancer is often treated with some combination of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Radiation_therapy\" title=\"Radiation therapy\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">radiation therapy</a>, surgery, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chemotherapy\" title=\"Chemotherapy\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">chemotherapy</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Targeted_therapy\" title=\"Targeted therapy\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">targeted therapy</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-7\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-TCT2018_4-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-TCT2018-4\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[4]</a></sup> Pain and symptom management are an important part of care.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-8\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup> <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Palliative_care\" title=\"Palliative care\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Palliative care</a>is particularly important in people with advanced disease.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-9\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup> The chance of survival depends on the type of cancer and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer_staging\" title=\"Cancer staging\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">extent of disease</a> at the start of treatment.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Bio_11-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Bio-11\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[11]</a></sup> In children under 15 at diagnosis, the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Five-year_survival_rate\" title=\"Five-year survival rate\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">five-year survival rate</a> in the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Developed_world\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Developed world\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">developed world</a> is on average 80%.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Peads_18-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Peads-18\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[18]</a></sup> For cancer in the United States, the average five-year survival rate is 66%.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Seer2014_5-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-Seer2014-5\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[5]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif;\">In 2015, about 90.5 million people had cancer.<sup id=\"cite_ref-GBD2015Pre_6-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-GBD2015Pre-6\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[6]</a></sup> About 14.1 million new cases occur a year (not including <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skin_cancer\" title=\"Skin cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">skin cancer ot</a></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif;\"><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" data-filename=\"3.jpg\" style=\"width: 240.788px; height: 160.74px;\"><br></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skin_cancer\" title=\"Skin cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">her than melanoma</a>).<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Bio_11-3\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Bio-11\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[11]</a></sup> It caused about 8.8 million deaths (15.7% of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Causes_of_death\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Causes of death\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">deaths</a>).<sup id=\"cite_ref-GBD2015De_7-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-GBD2015De-7\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[7]</a></sup> The most common types of cancer in males are <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lung_cancer\" title=\"Lung cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">lung cancer</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prostate_cancer\" title=\"Prostate cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">prostate cancer</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colorectal_cancer\" title=\"Colorectal cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">colorectal cancer</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stomach_cancer\" title=\"Stomach cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">stomach cancer</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014_19-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014-19\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[19]</a></sup> In females, the most common types are breast cancer, colorectal cancer, lung cancer and cervical cancer.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Bio_11-4\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Bio-11\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[11]</a></sup> If <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skin_cancer\" title=\"Skin cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">skin cancer</a> other than <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Melanoma\" title=\"Melanoma\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">melanoma</a> were included in total new cancer cases each year, it would account for around 40% of cases.<sup id=\"cite_ref-20\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-20\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[20]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Cak2012_21-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-Cak2012-21\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[21]</a></sup> In children, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Acute_lymphoblastic_leukemia\" title=\"Acute lymphoblastic leukemia\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">acute lymphoblastic leukemia</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brain_tumors\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brain tumors\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">brain tumors</a> are most common, except in Africa where <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-Hodgkin_lymphoma\" title=\"Non-Hodgkin lymphoma\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">non-Hodgkin lymphoma</a> occurs more often.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Peads_18-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Peads-18\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[18]</a></sup> In 2012, about 165,000 children under 15 years of age were diagnosed with cancer.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014_19-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014-19\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[19]</a></sup> The risk of cancer increases significantly with age, and many cancers occur more commonly in developed countries.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Bio_11-5\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Bio-11\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[11]</a></sup> Rates are increasing as <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Population_ageing\" title=\"Population ageing\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">more people live to an old age</a> and as lifestyle changes occur in the developing world.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Epi11_22-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-Epi11-22\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[22]</a></sup> The financial costs of cancer were estimated at $1.16 trillion <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_dollar\" title=\"United States dollar\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">USD</a> per year as of 2010.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Eco_23-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Eco-23\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[23]</a></sup></p>', '<p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif;\"><img src=\"data:image/jpeg;base64,\" data-filename=\"comment3.jpg\" style=\"width: 75px;\"><b><br></b></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif;\"><b>Cancer</b> is a group of diseases involving abnormal <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cell_growth\" title=\"Cell growth\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">cell growth</a> with the potential to invade or spread to other parts of the body.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-NCI2014_8-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-NCI2014-8\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[8]</a></sup> These contrast with <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Benign_tumor\" title=\"Benign tumor\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">benign tumors</a>, which do not spread.<sup id=\"cite_ref-NCI2014_8-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-NCI2014-8\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[8]</a></sup> Possible <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer_signs_and_symptoms\" title=\"Cancer signs and symptoms\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">signs and symptoms</a> include a lump, abnormal bleeding, prolonged cough, unexplained <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Weight_loss\" title=\"Weight loss\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">weight loss</a> and a change in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Defecation\" title=\"Defecation\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">bowel movements</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-NHS2012_1-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-NHS2012-1\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[1]</a></sup> While these symptoms may indicate cancer, they can also have other causes.<sup id=\"cite_ref-NHS2012_1-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-NHS2012-1\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[1]</a></sup> Over 100 types of cancers affect humans.<sup id=\"cite_ref-NCI2014_8-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-NCI2014-8\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[8]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Tobacco_use\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Tobacco use\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Tobacco use</a> is the cause of about 22% of cancer deaths.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-3\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup> Another 10% are due to <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Obesity\" title=\"Obesity\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">obesity</a>, poor <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diet_(nutrition)\" title=\"Diet (nutrition)\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">diet</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sedentary_lifestyle\" title=\"Sedentary lifestyle\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">lack of physical activity</a> or <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alcohol_abuse\" title=\"Alcohol abuse\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">excessive drinking</a> of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alcohol_(drug)\" title=\"Alcohol (drug)\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">alcohol</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-4\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-9\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-9\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[9]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-10\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-10\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[10]</a></sup> Other factors include certain infections, exposure to <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ionizing_radiation\" title=\"Ionizing radiation\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">ionizing radiation</a> and environmental pollutants.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Enviro2008_3-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-Enviro2008-3\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[3]</a></sup> In the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Developing_country\" title=\"Developing country\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">developing world</a>, 15% of cancers are due to infections such as <i><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Helicobacter_pylori\" title=\"Helicobacter pylori\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Helicobacter pylori</a></i>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hepatitis_B\" title=\"Hepatitis B\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">hepatitis B</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hepatitis_C\" title=\"Hepatitis C\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">hepatitis C</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Human_papillomavirus_infection\" title=\"Human papillomavirus infection\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">human papillomavirus infection</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Epstein%E2%80%93Barr_virus\" title=\"Epstein–Barr virus\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Epstein–Barr virus</a>and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/HIV\" title=\"HIV\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">human immunodeficiency virus</a> (HIV).<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-5\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup> These factors act, at least partly, by changing the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gene\" title=\"Gene\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">genes</a> of a cell.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Bio_11-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Bio-11\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[11]</a></sup> Typically, many genetic changes are required before cancer develops.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Bio_11-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Bio-11\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[11]</a></sup> Approximately 5–10% of cancers are due to inherited genetic defects from a person\'s parents.<sup id=\"cite_ref-ACS-heredity_12-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-ACS-heredity-12\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[12]</a></sup> Cancer can be detected by certain signs and symptoms or <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer_screening\" title=\"Cancer screening\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">screening tests</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-6\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup> It is then typically further investigated by <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Medical_imaging\" title=\"Medical imaging\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">medical imaging</a> and confirmed by <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Biopsy\" title=\"Biopsy\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">biopsy</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-13\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-13\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[13]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif;\">Many cancers can be prevented by not smoking, maintaining a healthy weight, not drinking too much <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Alcohol_(drug)\" title=\"Alcohol (drug)\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">alcohol</a>, eating plenty of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vegetables\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Vegetables\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">vegetables</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fruits\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Fruits\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">fruits</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Whole_grains\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Whole grains\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">whole grains</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vaccination\" title=\"Vaccination\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">vaccination</a> against certain infectious diseases, not eating too much <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Processed_meat\" title=\"Processed meat\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">processed</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Red_meat\" title=\"Red meat\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">red meat</a> and avoiding too much <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sunlight\" title=\"Sunlight\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">sunlight</a> exposure.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Kushi2012_14-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-Kushi2012-14\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[14]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-15\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-15\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[15]</a></sup> Early detection through <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer_screening\" title=\"Cancer screening\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">screening</a> is useful for <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cervical_cancer\" title=\"Cervical cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">cervical</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colorectal_cancer\" title=\"Colorectal cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">colorectal cancer</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Scr_16-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Scr-16\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[16]</a></sup> The benefits of screening in <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Breast_cancer\" title=\"Breast cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">breast cancer</a> are controversial.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Scr_16-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Scr-16\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[16]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Got2013_17-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-Got2013-17\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[17]</a></sup> Cancer is often treated with some combination of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Radiation_therapy\" title=\"Radiation therapy\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">radiation therapy</a>, surgery, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chemotherapy\" title=\"Chemotherapy\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">chemotherapy</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Targeted_therapy\" title=\"Targeted therapy\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">targeted therapy</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-7\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-TCT2018_4-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-TCT2018-4\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[4]</a></sup> Pain and symptom management are an important part of care.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-8\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup> <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Palliative_care\" title=\"Palliative care\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">Palliative care</a>is particularly important in people with advanced disease.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WHO2018_2-9\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WHO2018-2\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[2]</a></sup> The chance of survival depends on the type of cancer and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer_staging\" title=\"Cancer staging\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">extent of disease</a> at the start of treatment.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Bio_11-2\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Bio-11\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[11]</a></sup> In children under 15 at diagnosis, the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Five-year_survival_rate\" title=\"Five-year survival rate\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">five-year survival rate</a> in the <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Developed_world\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Developed world\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">developed world</a> is on average 80%.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Peads_18-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Peads-18\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[18]</a></sup> For cancer in the United States, the average five-year survival rate is 66%.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Seer2014_5-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-Seer2014-5\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[5]</a></sup></p><p style=\"margin-top: 0.5em; margin-bottom: 0.5em; line-height: inherit; color: rgb(34, 34, 34); font-family: sans-serif;\">In 2015, about 90.5 million people had cancer.<sup id=\"cite_ref-GBD2015Pre_6-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-GBD2015Pre-6\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[6]</a></sup> About 14.1 million new cases occur a year (not including <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skin_cancer\" title=\"Skin cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">skin cancer other than melanoma</a>).<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Bio_11-3\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Bio-11\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[11]</a></sup> It caused about 8.8 million deaths (15.7% of <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Causes_of_death\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Causes of death\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">deaths</a>).<sup id=\"cite_ref-GBD2015De_7-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-GBD2015De-7\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[7]</a></sup> The most common types of cancer in males are <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lung_cancer\" title=\"Lung cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">lung cancer</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Prostate_cancer\" title=\"Prostate cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">prostate cancer</a>, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colorectal_cancer\" title=\"Colorectal cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">colorectal cancer</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stomach_cancer\" title=\"Stomach cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">stomach cancer</a>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014_19-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014-19\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[19]</a></sup> In females, the most common types are breast cancer, colorectal cancer, lung cancer and cervical cancer.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Bio_11-4\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Bio-11\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[11]</a></sup> If <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skin_cancer\" title=\"Skin cancer\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">skin cancer</a> other than <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Melanoma\" title=\"Melanoma\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">melanoma</a> were included in total new cancer cases each year, it would account for around 40% of cases.<sup id=\"cite_ref-20\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-20\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[20]</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-Cak2012_21-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-Cak2012-21\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[21]</a></sup> In children, <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Acute_lymphoblastic_leukemia\" title=\"Acute lymphoblastic leukemia\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">acute lymphoblastic leukemia</a> and <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Brain_tumors\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Brain tumors\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">brain tumors</a> are most common, except in Africa where <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Non-Hodgkin_lymphoma\" title=\"Non-Hodgkin lymphoma\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">non-Hodgkin lymphoma</a> occurs more often.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Peads_18-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Peads-18\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[18]</a></sup> In 2012, about 165,000 children under 15 years of age were diagnosed with cancer.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014_19-1\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014-19\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[19]</a></sup> The risk of cancer increases significantly with age, and many cancers occur more commonly in developed countries.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Bio_11-5\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Bio-11\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[11]</a></sup> Rates are increasing as <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Population_ageing\" title=\"Population ageing\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">more people live to an old age</a> and as lifestyle changes occur in the developing world.<sup id=\"cite_ref-Epi11_22-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-Epi11-22\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[22]</a></sup> The financial costs of cancer were estimated at $1.16 trillion <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/United_States_dollar\" title=\"United States dollar\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">USD</a> per year as of 2010.<sup id=\"cite_ref-WCR2014Eco_23-0\" class=\"reference\" style=\"line-height: 1; unicode-bidi: isolate; white-space: nowrap; font-size: 11.2px;\"><a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cancer#cite_note-WCR2014Eco-23\" style=\"color: rgb(11, 0, 128); background-image: none; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\">[23]</a></sup></p>', 'big4.jpg', '2019-03-26 13:00:16', '2019-03-26 13:00:52', 1, 'yes');
